{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[B5]  She stood there bright as the sun on that [E/B]California coast.
[A/B]  He was a Midwestern boy on his [B5]own.    [B5]
[B5]  She looked at him with those soft eyes, so [E/B]innocent and blue.
[A/B]  He knew right then he was too far from [B5]home.    [B5]

[B5]  Oh,  [E/B] he was too far from [A/B]home.   [B5]
{end_of_verse}


{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[B5]  She took his hand and she led him a[E/B]long that golden beach.
[A/B]  They watched the waves tumble over the [B5]sand.   [B5]
[B5]  They drove for miles and miles up those [E/B]twisting, turning roads.
[A/B]  Higher and higher and higher they [B5]climbed.   [B5]
{end_of_verse}


{start_of_chorus: Chorus}
