{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[B5]  He'd headed west 'cause he felt that a [E/B]change would do him good.
[A/B]  See some old friends, good for the [B5]soul.    [B5]
[B5]  She had been born with a face that would let [E/B]her get her way.
[A/B]  He saw that face and he lost all control.   [B5]

[B5]  Yeah,  [E/B] He had lost all [A/B]control.   [B5]
{end_of_verse}


{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
[B5]  Night after night, day after [E/B]day, it went on and on.
[A/B]  Then came that morning he woke up alone.
[B5]  He spent all night staring down at the [E/B]lights of L.A.
[A/B]  Wondering if he could ever go [B5]home.
{end_of_verse}


